{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Dishonest scales are an abomination to the Lord,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "But a just weight is His delight.",
          "speaker": "The Lord"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When pride comes, then comes shame;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But with the humble is wisdom."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The integrity of the upright will guide them,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the perversity of the unfaithful will destroy them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Riches do not profit in the day of wrath,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But righteousness delivers from death."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The righteousness of the blameless will direct his way aright,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the wicked will fall by his own wickedness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The righteousness of the upright will deliver them,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the unfaithful will be caught by their lust."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When a wicked man dies, his expectation will perish,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the hope of the unjust perishes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The righteous is delivered from trouble,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And it comes to the wicked instead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The hypocrite with his mouth destroys his neighbor,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But through knowledge the righteous will be delivered."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when the wicked perish, there is jubilation."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who is devoid of wisdom despises his neighbor,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But a man of understanding holds his peace."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A talebearer reveals secrets,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he who is of a faithful spirit conceals a matter."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Where there is no counsel, the people fall;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But in the multitude of counselors there is safety."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who is surety for a stranger will suffer,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But one who hates being surety is secure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A gracious woman retains honor,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But ruthless men retain riches."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The merciful man does good for his own soul,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he who is cruel troubles his own flesh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The wicked man does deceptive work,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he who sows righteousness will have a sure reward."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "As righteousness leads to life,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So he who pursues evil pursues it to his own death."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Those who are of a perverse heart are an abomination to the Lord,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "But the blameless in their ways are His delight.",
          "speaker": "The Lord"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Though they join forces, the wicked will not go unpunished;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the posterity of the righteous will be delivered."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "As a ring of gold in a swine's snout, So is a lovely woman who lacks discretion."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The desire of the righteous is only good,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the expectation of the wicked is wrath."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "There is one who scatters, yet increases more;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And there is one who withholds more than is right, But it leads to poverty."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The generous soul will be made rich,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he who waters will also be watered himself."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The people will curse him who withholds grain,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But blessing will be on the head of him who sells it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who earnestly seeks good finds favor,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But trouble will come to him who seeks evil."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who trusts in his riches will fall,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the righteous will flourish like foliage."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who troubles his own house will inherit the wind,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the fool will be servant to the wise of heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he who wins souls is wise."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If the righteous will be recompensed on the earth,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "How much more the ungodly and the sinner."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}